Sentencas: Solid oxide cells (SOCs) which can be operated as a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) and solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC) have tremendous attention as a next-generation energy device.
Titulo: Dysprosium doping effects on perovskite oxides for air and fuel electrodes of solid oxide cells

Sentencas: To improve the SOCs, recently the atmospheric adaptive materials (AAMs) which can change the crystal structure by themselves to the atmosphere have been studied and reported.
Titulo: Dysprosium doping effects on perovskite oxides for air and fuel electrodes of solid oxide cells

Sentencas: As an approach to develop the AAMs, the Dy doping strategy was applied to both air and fuel electrodes for SOCs with various doping amounts from 0 to 50 wt%.
Titulo: Dysprosium doping effects on perovskite oxides for air and fuel electrodes of solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Among the samples, the 10% Dy doped Pr0.5Ba0.5MnO3-delta shows the best improvements on the catalytic properties and electrochemical performances for both air and fuel electrode.
Titulo: Dysprosium doping effects on perovskite oxides for air and fuel electrodes of solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The symmetrical cell with the 10 wt% Dy doped Pr0.5Ba0.5MnO3-delta exhibits the maximum power density of 0.175 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C in SOFC mode and current density of 0.554 A cm(-2) at 850 degrees C at 1.5 V in SOEC mode, respectively.
Titulo: Dysprosium doping effects on perovskite oxides for air and fuel electrodes of solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The study demonstrates that the Dy doping strategy is effective on both air and fuel electrodes and is a promising approach to improve the electrochemical performances for both SOFC and SOEC.
Titulo: Dysprosium doping effects on perovskite oxides for air and fuel electrodes of solid oxide cells
